Homage to John Paul II on which, from time to time, the odd crow lands to poop. Taking into account that in some cultures the crow is the representation of death, this scene reminds us that no one, no matter how great they were in life, escapes their final date with death to whom we must be accountable. So enjoy what you have in life and don't think so much about retirement because you never know when the one with the scythe will visit us. A few meters away, an always smiling straw gardener contemplates the scene with amusement since he knows that, as an inert being, the one with the scythe will leave him alone.
